The disinfectant is seen as providing protection against the spread of the disease, although its effectiveness has not yet been scientifically proven. In China, demand for Dettol-branded hand gels is outstripping supply, owner Reckitt Benckiser has said. The shortages come as global markets slump for a sixth day, with the FTSE 100 down more than 3%. Luxury carmaker Aston Martin and drinks giant Anheuser-Busch InBev are the latest to warn of the virus's impact on their businesses.

He added the firm had "seen some disruptions to retail and distribution channels and getting products in to market", meaning the effect on company performance had been balanced.
